  "prompt": "What should every first time anime convention goer know?",
  "response": "Attending an anime convention for the first time can be a thrilling experience! Here are some tips to make the most of your trip:\n\n1. **Plan Ahead:** Check the convention schedule and plan which panels, screenings, and events you want to attend. Prioritize your must-sees but leave some flexibility for spontaneous activities.\n\n2. **Budget:** Consider all expenses, including tickets, transportation, accommodation, food, and spending money for merchandise or artist alley purchases.\n\n3. **Cosplay Considerations:** If you're cosplaying, make sure your costume is comfortable and practical for long periods. Pack an emergency repair kit with safety pins, glue, and sewing supplies.\n\n4. **Comfort:** Wear comfortable shoes since you'll likely be walking and standing a lot. Pack layers if the convention center is cold and stay hydrated.\n\n5. **Essentials:** Bring a backpack with snacks, water, a phone charger, spare clothes, and any personal items you might need. \n\n6. **Etiquette:** Respect personal space and ask permission before taking photos of cosplayers. Be polite to staff and other attendees.\n\n7. **Time Management:** Lines for popular events can be long, so manage your time wisely. Arrive early for high-demand panels and screenings.\n\n8. **Safety:** Keep your belongings secure and be aware of your surroundings. If you\u2019re traveling alone, let someone know your plans and check in with them regularly.\n\n9. **Networking:** Anime conventions are a great place to meet like-minded people. Be open to making new friends and joining in discussions.\n\n10. **Enjoy Yourself:** Don't stress too much about following a strict schedule. The goal is to have fun and enjoy the experience!\n\nBy keeping these tips in mind, your first anime convention should be an unforgettable adventure!",
